==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Springy
<hw>Spring"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Springier</adjf>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Springiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Spring</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Resembling, having the qualities of, or pertaining to,
a spring; elastic; <as>as, <ex>springy</ex> steel; a <ex>springy</ex>
step.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though her little frame was slight, it was firm and
<qex>springy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abounding with springs or fountains; wet; spongy;
<as>as, <ex>springy</ex> land</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprinkle</ent>⟦br⟧
